[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":1491},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2025\u002F05\u002F13\u002Ftest-api-without-postman-using-curl\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2025\u002F05\u002F13\u002Ftest-api-without-postman-using-curl\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2025\u002F05\u002F13\u002Ftest-api-without-postman-using-curl\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2025\u002F05\u002F13\u002Ftest-api-without-postman-using-curl\u002F":1467,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2025\u002F05\u002F13\u002Ftest-api-without-postman-using-curl\u002F":1476},"\u002Fother\u002F20250513\u002F3343643828\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":1449,"date":1450,"description":1451,"extension":1452,"lang":1453,"meta":1454,"navigation":1455,"path":1456,"readingMinutes":1457,"seo":1458,"standalone":1459,"stem":1460,"tags":1461,"tldr":1464,"updated":1450,"url":1465,"__hash__":1466},"content\u002Fen\u002FMisc\u002Ftest-api-without-postman-using-curl.md","No Postman? No Problem — Testing APIs with curl","8462017593",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":1432},"minimark",[11,19,24,31,35,43,61,72,78,81,166,169,175,184,190,193,197,200,213,216,232,235,247,257,270,275,280,283,337,340,347,364,374,388,400,407,427,434,476,479,485,492,523,530,571,575,582,610,616,622,627,647,652,663,696,700,707,726,729,733,742,765,768,801,808,853,858,866,893,899,906,996,999,1003,1006,1054,1062,1066,1072,1102,1106,1115,1138,1140,1188,1190,1194,1200,1215,1220,1225,1229,1236,1253,1261,1265,1271,1288,1293,1296,1300,1303,1428],[12,13,14],"p",{},[15,16],"img",{"alt":17,"src":18},"curl","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fcurl\u002FChatGPT%20Image%202025%E5%B9%B45%E6%9C%8814%E6%97%A5%20%E4%B8%8B%E5%8D%8811_01_19.png",[20,21,23],"h2",{"id":22},"intro","Intro",[12,25,26,27,30],{},"Sometimes you can't use Postman to test an API, and you can't install other tools either — maybe you're SSH'd into a server (servers usually have no GUI). That's when ",[28,29,17],"code",{}," is your friend.",[20,32,34],{"id":33},"what-is-curl","What is curl?",[12,36,37,38,42],{},"curl is short for ",[39,40,41],"strong",{},"Client URL",". It's a network protocol tool that supports a huge range of protocols — FTP, FTPS, HTTP, HTTPS, and many more. Almost any network protocol you can think of, curl can test.",[44,45,48],"callout",{"title":46,"type":47},"Note","note",[12,49,50,51,53,54,57,58,60],{},"Some people write ",[28,52,17],{},", others write ",[28,55,56],{},"cURL",". I'll stick with ",[28,59,17],{}," throughout this post.",[12,62,63,64,71],{},"You'll see curl all over the place. For example, the ",[65,66,70],"a",{"href":67,"rel":68},"https:\u002F\u002Fhexschool.github.io\u002Fec-courses-api-swaggerDoc\u002F#\u002F",[69],"nofollow","Hexschool Swagger API docs",":",[12,73,74],{},[15,75],{"alt":76,"src":77},"Swagger API testing","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fcurl\u002F20250514214238.png",[12,79,80],{},"At the bottom you'll see something like:",[82,83,88],"pre",{"className":84,"code":85,"language":86,"meta":87,"style":87},"language-bash shiki shiki-themes github-light github-light github-dark-high-contrast","curl -X 'POST' \\\n  'https:\u002F\u002Fec-course-api.hexschool.io\u002Fv2\u002Fadmin\u002Fsignin' \\\n  -H 'accept: application\u002Fjson' \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application\u002Fjson' \\\n  -d '{\n  \"username\": \"example@test.com\",\n  \"password\": \"example\"\n}'\n","bash","",[28,89,90,110,118,129,139,148,154,160],{"__ignoreMap":87},[91,92,95,98,102,106],"span",{"class":93,"line":94},"line",1,[91,96,17],{"class":97},"smYoP",[91,99,101],{"class":100},"stw71"," -X",[91,103,105],{"class":104},"sWayO"," 'POST'",[91,107,109],{"class":108},"sbsOT"," \\\n",[91,111,113,116],{"class":93,"line":112},2,[91,114,115],{"class":104},"  'https:\u002F\u002Fec-course-api.hexschool.io\u002Fv2\u002Fadmin\u002Fsignin'",[91,117,109],{"class":108},[91,119,121,124,127],{"class":93,"line":120},3,[91,122,123],{"class":100},"  -H",[91,125,126],{"class":104}," 'accept: application\u002Fjson'",[91,128,109],{"class":108},[91,130,132,134,137],{"class":93,"line":131},4,[91,133,123],{"class":100},[91,135,136],{"class":104}," 'Content-Type: application\u002Fjson'",[91,138,109],{"class":108},[91,140,142,145],{"class":93,"line":141},5,[91,143,144],{"class":100},"  -d",[91,146,147],{"class":104}," '{\n",[91,149,151],{"class":93,"line":150},6,[91,152,153],{"class":104},"  \"username\": \"example@test.com\",\n",[91,155,157],{"class":93,"line":156},7,[91,158,159],{"class":104},"  \"password\": \"example\"\n",[91,161,163],{"class":93,"line":162},8,[91,164,165],{"class":104},"}'\n",[12,167,168],{},"You can copy that straight into a terminal and run it.",[12,170,171],{},[15,172],{"alt":173,"src":174},"Terminal","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fcurl\u002F20250514214527.png",[12,176,177,178,183],{},"Where else? In ",[65,179,182],{"href":180,"rel":181},"https:\u002F\u002Fisraynotarray.com\u002Fother\u002F20211207\u002F427026\u002F",[69],"Postman (article in Mandarin)"," — after you test an API in Postman, click the \"Code\" button and you can see the curl equivalent.",[12,185,186],{},[15,187],{"alt":188,"src":189},"Postman","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fcurl\u002F20250514214815.png",[12,191,192],{},"Let's go through how to actually use it.",[20,194,196],{"id":195},"curl-syntax","curl syntax",[12,198,199],{},"curl's syntax is simple. If you're just testing a GET API, this line does it:",[82,201,203],{"className":84,"code":202,"language":86,"meta":87,"style":87},"curl [URL]\n",[28,204,205],{"__ignoreMap":87},[91,206,207,209],{"class":93,"line":94},[91,208,17],{"class":97},[91,210,212],{"class":211},"s8XSl"," [URL]\n",[12,214,215],{},"But in practice you'll need to pass parameters:",[217,218,219,223,226,229],"ul",{},[220,221,222],"li",{},"HTTP methods like POST, GET, PUT, DELETE",[220,224,225],{},"Headers",[220,227,228],{},"Body data",[220,230,231],{},"Other options",[12,233,234],{},"So the typical curl invocation looks like:",[82,236,238],{"className":84,"code":237,"language":86,"meta":87,"style":87},"curl [options] [URL]\n",[28,239,240],{"__ignoreMap":87},[91,241,242,244],{"class":93,"line":94},[91,243,17],{"class":97},[91,245,246],{"class":211}," [options] [URL]\n",[12,248,249,252,253,256],{},[28,250,251],{},"options"," are the flags you pass; ",[28,254,255],{},"URL"," is the target. Don't worry about the flags yet — I'll walk through CRUD examples.",[12,258,259,260,263,264,269],{},"I'll use Hexschool's practice TodoList API as the example. Base path: ",[28,261,262],{},"https:\u002F\u002Ftodolist-api.hexschool.io\u002F",". API docs: ",[65,265,268],{"href":266,"rel":267},"https:\u002F\u002Ftodolist-api.hexschool.io\u002Fdoc\u002F",[69],"here",".",[44,271,272],{"title":46,"type":47},[12,273,274],{},"Since this is a practice API, data gets wiped every day at 1:15 AM.",[276,277,279],"h3",{"id":278},"register-an-account-post-userssign_up","Register an account (POST \u002Fusers\u002Fsign_up)",[12,281,282],{},"First we need to register an account. From the docs, sign-up takes these params:",[82,284,288],{"className":285,"code":286,"language":287,"meta":87,"style":87},"language-json shiki shiki-themes github-light github-light github-dark-high-contrast","{\n  \"email\": \"example@gmail.com\",\n  \"password\": \"example\",\n  \"nickname\": \"example\"\n}\n","json",[28,289,290,295,310,322,332],{"__ignoreMap":87},[91,291,292],{"class":93,"line":94},[91,293,294],{"class":211},"{\n",[91,296,297,301,304,307],{"class":93,"line":112},[91,298,300],{"class":299},"sWTrB","  \"email\"",[91,302,303],{"class":211},": ",[91,305,306],{"class":104},"\"example@gmail.com\"",[91,308,309],{"class":211},",\n",[91,311,312,315,317,320],{"class":93,"line":120},[91,313,314],{"class":299},"  \"password\"",[91,316,303],{"class":211},[91,318,319],{"class":104},"\"example\"",[91,321,309],{"class":211},[91,323,324,327,329],{"class":93,"line":131},[91,325,326],{"class":299},"  \"nickname\"",[91,328,303],{"class":211},[91,330,331],{"class":104},"\"example\"\n",[91,333,334],{"class":93,"line":141},[91,335,336],{"class":211},"}\n",[12,338,339],{},"How do we call this with curl?",[12,341,342,343,346],{},"The ",[28,344,345],{},"-X"," flag specifies the HTTP method. We want POST, so:",[82,348,350],{"className":84,"code":349,"language":86,"meta":87,"style":87},"curl -X POST https:\u002F\u002Ftodolist-api.hexschool.io\u002Fusers\u002Fsign_up\n",[28,351,352],{"__ignoreMap":87},[91,353,354,356,358,361],{"class":93,"line":94},[91,355,17],{"class":97},[91,357,101],{"class":100},[91,359,360],{"class":104}," POST",[91,362,363],{"class":104}," https:\u002F\u002Ftodolist-api.hexschool.io\u002Fusers\u002Fsign_up\n",[12,365,366,367,370,371,71],{},"To shorten it, you can drop the space: ",[28,368,369],{},"-X POST"," becomes ",[28,372,373],{},"-XPOST",[82,375,377],{"className":84,"code":376,"language":86,"meta":87,"style":87},"curl -XPOST https:\u002F\u002Ftodolist-api.hexschool.io\u002Fusers\u002Fsign_up\n",[28,378,379],{"__ignoreMap":87},[91,380,381,383,386],{"class":93,"line":94},[91,382,17],{"class":97},[91,384,385],{"class":100}," -XPOST",[91,387,363],{"class":104},[44,389,390],{"title":46,"type":47},[12,391,342,392,395,396,399],{},[28,393,394],{},"X"," must be uppercase. Lowercase ",[28,397,398],{},"-x"," is a different flag — it sets a proxy.",[12,401,402,403,406],{},"Now we need to tell the server we're sending JSON. The ",[28,404,405],{},"-H"," flag adds a header:",[82,408,410],{"className":84,"code":409,"language":86,"meta":87,"style":87},"curl -XPOST https:\u002F\u002Ftodolist-api.hexschool.io\u002Fusers\u002Fsign_up -H \"Content-Type: application\u002Fjson\"\n",[28,411,412],{"__ignoreMap":87},[91,413,414,416,418,421,424],{"class":93,"line":94},[91,415,17],{"class":97},[91,417,385],{"class":100},[91,419,420],{"class":104}," https:\u002F\u002Ftodolist-api.hexschool.io\u002Fusers\u002Fsign_up",[91,422,423],{"class":100}," -H",[91,425,426],{"class":104}," \"Content-Type: application\u002Fjson\"\n",[12,428,429,430,433],{},"How do we pass the body? The ",[28,431,432],{},"-d"," flag:",[82,435,437],{"className":84,"code":436,"language":86,"meta":87,"style":87},"curl -XPOST https:\u002F\u002Ftodolist-api.hexschool.io\u002Fusers\u002Fsign_up -H \"Content-Type: application\u002Fjson\" -d '{\n  \"email\": \"example@gmail.com\",\n  \"password\": \"example\",\n  \"nickname\": \"example\"\n}'\n",[28,438,439,457,462,467,472],{"__ignoreMap":87},[91,440,441,443,445,447,449,452,455],{"class":93,"line":94},[91,442,17],{"class":97},[91,444,385],{"class":100},[91,446,420],{"class":104},[91,448,423],{"class":100},[91,450,451],{"class":104}," \"Content-Type: application\u002Fjson\"",[91,453,454],{"class":100}," -d",[91,456,147],{"class":104},[91,458,459],{"class":93,"line":112},[91,460,461],{"class":104},"  \"email\": \"example@gmail.com\",\n",[91,463,464],{"class":93,"line":120},[91,465,466],{"class":104},"  \"password\": \"example\",\n",[91,468,469],{"class":93,"line":131},[91,470,471],{"class":104},"  \"nickname\": \"example\"\n",[91,473,474],{"class":93,"line":141},[91,475,165],{"class":104},[12,477,478],{},"Paste that in the terminal and the account gets created.",[12,480,481],{},[15,482],{"alt":483,"src":484},"Sign-up success","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fcurl\u002F20250514220226.png",[12,486,487,488,491],{},"Mini-exercise: sign-in is the same pattern. The endpoint is ",[28,489,490],{},"POST \u002Fusers\u002Fsign_in",", with this payload:",[82,493,495],{"className":285,"code":494,"language":287,"meta":87,"style":87},"{\n  \"email\": \"example@gmail.com\",\n  \"password\": \"example\"\n}\n",[28,496,497,501,511,519],{"__ignoreMap":87},[91,498,499],{"class":93,"line":94},[91,500,294],{"class":211},[91,502,503,505,507,509],{"class":93,"line":112},[91,504,300],{"class":299},[91,506,303],{"class":211},[91,508,306],{"class":104},[91,510,309],{"class":211},[91,512,513,515,517],{"class":93,"line":120},[91,514,314],{"class":299},[91,516,303],{"class":211},[91,518,331],{"class":104},[91,520,521],{"class":93,"line":131},[91,522,336],{"class":211},[12,524,525,526,529],{},"On success it returns a ",[28,527,528],{},"token",", which you'll need to authenticate other API calls. Try writing the curl yourself.",[531,532,533,537],"details",{},[534,535,536],"summary",{},"Click for the answer (try first!)",[82,538,540],{"className":84,"code":539,"language":86,"meta":87,"style":87},"curl -XPOST https:\u002F\u002Ftodolist-api.hexschool.io\u002Fusers\u002Fsign_in -H \"Content-Type: application\u002Fjson\" -d '{\n  \"email\": \"example@gmail.com\",\n  \"password\": \"example\"\n}'\n",[28,541,542,559,563,567],{"__ignoreMap":87},[91,543,544,546,548,551,553,555,557],{"class":93,"line":94},[91,545,17],{"class":97},[91,547,385],{"class":100},[91,549,550],{"class":104}," https:\u002F\u002Ftodolist-api.hexschool.io\u002Fusers\u002Fsign_in",[91,552,423],{"class":100},[91,554,451],{"class":104},[91,556,454],{"class":100},[91,558,147],{"class":104},[91,560,561],{"class":93,"line":112},[91,562,461],{"class":104},[91,564,565],{"class":93,"line":120},[91,566,159],{"class":104},[91,568,569],{"class":93,"line":131},[91,570,165],{"class":104},[276,572,574],{"id":573},"verify-token-get-userscheckout","Verify token (GET \u002Fusers\u002Fcheckout)",[12,576,577,578,581],{},"This one's simpler — it's a GET, so we don't typically send a body. From the docs, you put the token from sign-in into the ",[28,579,580],{},"Authorization"," header:",[82,583,585],{"className":84,"code":584,"language":86,"meta":87,"style":87},"curl -XGET https:\u002F\u002Ftodolist-api.hexschool.io\u002Fusers\u002Fcheckout -H \"Content-Type: application\u002Fjson\" -H \"Authorization: {{ token }}\" # ← replace {{ token }} with the actual JWT\n",[28,586,587],{"__ignoreMap":87},[91,588,589,591,594,597,599,601,603,606],{"class":93,"line":94},[91,590,17],