te the response to a file",[12,1230,1231,1232,1235],{},"If the response is long, use ",[28,1233,1234],{},"-o"," to write it to a file:",[82,1237,1239],{"className":84,"code":1238,"language":86,"meta":87,"style":87},"curl -o google.html https:\u002F\u002Fgoogle.com\n",[28,1240,1241],{"__ignoreMap":87},[91,1242,1243,1245,1248,1251],{"class":93,"line":94},[91,1244,17],{"class":97},[91,1246,1247],{"class":100}," -o",[91,1249,1250],{"class":104}," google.html",[91,1252,1214],{"class":104},[12,1254,1255,1257,1258,269],{},[28,1256,1234],{}," takes the filename. The response gets written to ",[28,1259,1260],{},"google.html",[20,1262,1264],{"id":1263},"set-a-user-agent","Set a User-Agent",[12,1266,1267,1268,71],{},"Can you set a User-Agent (tell the server who you are, what browser)? Yes — use ",[28,1269,1270],{},"-A",[82,1272,1274],{"className":84,"code":1273,"language":86,"meta":87,"style":87},"curl -A \"Mozilla\u002F5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit\u002F537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome\u002F58.0.3029.110 Safari\u002F537.3\" https:\u002F\u002Fgoogle.com\n",[28,1275,1276],{"__ignoreMap":87},[91,1277,1278,1280,1283,1286],{"class":93,"line":94},[91,1279,17],{"class":97},[91,1281,1282],{"class":100}," -A",[91,1284,1285],{"class":104}," \"Mozilla\u002F5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit\u002F537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome\u002F58.0.3029.110 Safari\u002F537.3\"",[91,1287,1214],{"class":104},[12,1289,1290,1292],{},[28,1291,1270],{}," takes the User-Agent string.",[12,1294,1295],{},"Why mention this? Because some sites restrict access based on unknown User-Agents, so you might need to spoof one.",[20,1297,1299],{"id":1298},"wrapping-up","Wrapping up",[12,1301,1302],{},"Quick reference table for everything covered:",[1304,1305,1306,1322],"table",{},[1307,1308,1309],"thead",{},[1310,1311,1312,1316,1319],"tr",{},[1313,1314,1315],"th",{},"Flag",[1313,1317,1318],{},"What it does",[1313,1320,1321],{},"Example",[1323,1324,1325,1340,1357,1371,1385,1399,1413],"tbody",{},[1310,1326,1327,1332,1335],{},[1328,1329,1330],"td",{},[28,1331,345],{},[1328,1333,1334],{},"Set HTTP method (POST, PUT, DELETE, etc.)",[1328,1336,1337],{},[28,1338,1339],{},"curl -XPOST https:\u002F\u002Fapi.example.com\u002Fitems",[1310,1341,1342,1346,1352],{},[1328,1343,1344],{},[28,1345,405],{},[1328,1347,1348,1349,1351],{},"Add a header (one ",[28,1350,405],{}," per header)",[1328,1353,1354],{},[28,1355,1356],{},"curl -H \"Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN\"",[1310,1358,1359,1363,1366],{},[1328,1360,1361],{},[28,1362,432],{},[1328,1364,1365],{},"Send body data (POST\u002FPUT)",[1328,1367,1368],{},[28,1369,1370],{},"curl -d '{\"content\":\"Buy dinner\"}' -H \"Content-Type: application\u002Fjson\" https:\u002F\u002Fapi.example.com\u002Ftodos",[1310,1372,1373,1377,1380],{},[1328,1374,1375],{},[28,1376,1199],{},[1328,1378,1379],{},"Show verbose connection details (request\u002Fresponse headers, etc.)",[1328,1381,1382],{},[28,1383,1384],{},"curl -v https:\u002F\u002Fexample.com",[1310,1386,1387,1391,1394],{},[1328,1388,1389],{},[28,1390,1234],{},[1328,1392,1393],{},"Write response to a file",[1328,1395,1396],{},[28,1397,1398],{},"curl -o result.html https:\u002F\u002Fexample.com",[1310,1400,1401,1405,1408],{},[1328,1402,1403],{},[28,1404,1270],{},[1328,1406,1407],{},"Set User-Agent (mimic a browser\u002Fdevice)",[1328,1409,1410],{},[28,1411,1412],{},"curl -A \"Mozilla\u002F5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64)\" https:\u002F\u002Fexample.com",[1310,1414,1415,1420,1423],{},[1328,1416,1417,1419],{},[28,1418,806],{}," (backslash)",[1328,1421,1422],{},"Line continuation for readable multi-line curl",[1328,1424,1425],{},[28,1426,1427],{},"curl -XPOST https:\u002F\u002Fapi.example.com \\  -H \"Authorization: Bearer ...\" \\  -d '{\"key\":\"value\"}'",[1429,1430,1431],"style",{},"html pre.shiki code .smYoP, html code.shiki .smYoP{--shiki-light:#6F42C1;--shiki-default:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#FFB757}html pre.shiki code .stw71, html code.shiki .stw71{--shiki-light:#005CC5;--